original: Buttle, Guldrupe, Sjonhem o. Viklau sed. 43. Mil :pastor v. Gotl. inf :reg. sed. 39. Medl. av Frimurarorden. Skr.: Falska profeter. Ett ord om Jehovas vittnen (44) samt art. o. rec. i dagspressen o. olika kyrkl. tidskr. m. m.
translated: Buttle, born in the village of Guldrupe, lived in the parishes of Sjonhem and Viklau since 1943. He served as a pastor in the Gotland Infantry Regiment from 1939. He was a member of the Freemason's Order and wrote a publication called "False Prophets" and an article about Jehovah's Witnesses in 1944. He also wrote articles and reviews for various newspapers and church publications.

worksWritten.name: Articles and reviews for various newspapers and church publications
